[src:randomized-algorithms-deep/chernoff-bound] In general, unfortunately, a dependence on $\log(\min(d_{1},d_{2}))$ is inevitable: take for example a diagonal random sign matrix of dimension $d\times d$ .
[src:randomized-algorithms-deep/chernoff-bound] The operator norm of the sum of *t* independent samples is precisely the maximum deviation among *d* independent random walks of length *t*.
[src:randomized-algorithms-deep/chernoff-bound] In order to achieve a fixed bound on the maximum deviation with constant probability, it is easy to see that *t* should grow logarithmically with *d* in this scenario.
