[src:randomized-algorithms-deep/randomized-algorithm] The probability that the algorithm succeeds is 1 − the probability that all attempts fail.
[src:randomized-algorithms-deep/randomized-algorithm] By lemma 1, the probability that *C**i* = *C* is the probability that no edge of *C* is selected during iteration *i*.
[src:randomized-algorithms-deep/randomized-algorithm] Consider the inner loop and let *G**j* denote the graph after *j* edge contractions, where *j* ∈ {0, 1, …, *n* − 3}.
[src:randomized-algorithms-deep/randomized-algorithm] We use the chain rule of conditional possibilities.
